# ============================================================================
#  .deploy.env.example  —  template. Copy to .deploy.env (gitignored) and fill
#  in the 4 values below.
#
#      cp .deploy.env.example .deploy.env
#
#  These drive a non-interactive (Cloudflare API) deploy via wrangler — no
#  browser `wrangler login`. Keeping the real values in the gitignored
#  .deploy.env keeps secrets out of the repo. Never commit .deploy.env.
# ============================================================================
#
#  HOW TO FILL EACH VALUE
#  ----------------------
#  CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
#    dash.cloudflare.com → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token →
#    "Edit Cloudflare Workers" template. That template covers everything this
#    deploy touches: Workers Scripts, KV Storage, Durable Objects.
#
#  CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
#    dash.cloudflare.com → Workers & Pages → "Account ID" in the right sidebar.
#
#  SIMPLENOTE_TOKEN
#    Simperium token for your Simplenote account (see .dev.vars.example for how
#    to obtain it via the sn CLI).
#
#  ACCESS_PASSWORD
#    You choose this. It's the shared password that gates the OAuth login when
#    you add the connector in Claude.ai.
#
#  DEPLOY FLOW (what these values are used for)
#  -------------------------------------------
#    1. Verify token   — `wrangler whoami` (confirms auth + account)
#    2. KV namespace   — create OAUTH_KV, patch id into wrangler.jsonc
#    3. Secrets        — push SIMPLENOTE_TOKEN + ACCESS_PASSWORD via secret put
#    4. Deploy         — `wrangler deploy`, yields the *.workers.dev URL
#    5. Live test      — probe /mcp (expect 401), /authorize login gate, and
#                        OAuth metadata to confirm it's serving
# ============================================================================

# --- Cloudflare API auth (drives wrangler without `wrangler login`) ---
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# --- Worker secrets (pushed via `wrangler secret put`) ---
SIMPLENOTE_TOKEN=
ACCESS_PASSWORD=
